WEBVTT

1
00:00:08.003 --> 00:00:18.379
These subtitles are intended for the
23.976 fps. 1h53m07s version of the video

2
00:01:53.231 --> 00:01:54.232
Bingo.

3
00:02:09.497 --> 00:02:11.145
Fucking hell.

4
00:02:13.334 --> 00:02:14.949
Fucking hell.

5
00:03:05.505 --> 00:03:06.423
Oh. God.

6
00:03:06.506 --> 00:03:08.049
Keep your shit together...

7
00:03:08.133 --> 00:03:10.301
if you wanna get 'em out of here.

8
00:03:12.345 --> 00:03:13.805
I can pop these. no problem!

9
00:03:13.888 --> 00:03:14.848
So get to it!

10
00:03:29.112 --> 00:03:30.155
Security. we have a break-in.

11
00:03:30.238 --> 00:03:31.573
Get to sector—

12
00:03:39.873 --> 00:03:41.916
I know who you are.

13
00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:43.251
I know what you
think you're doing—

14
00:03:43.334 --> 00:03:44.294
If you don't wanna get hurt...

15
00:03:44.377 --> 00:03:45.336
keep your mouth shut...

16
00:03:45.420 --> 00:03:46.880
and don't move a fuckin' muscle.

17
00:03:46.963 --> 00:03:48.423
The chimps are infected!

18
00:03:48.839 --> 00:03:51.009
They're highly contagious.

19
00:03:51.092 --> 00:03:52.218
They've been given an inhibitor.

20
00:03:52.302 --> 00:03:53.303
Infected with what?

21
00:03:53.386 --> 00:03:55.764
In order to cure.
you must first understand.

22
00:03:55.847 --> 00:03:57.599
Infected with what?!

23
00:04:00.602 --> 00:04:01.853
Rage.

24
00:04:04.272 --> 00:04:05.940
What the fuck he's talking about?!

25
00:04:06.024 --> 00:04:07.066
We don't have time for this!

26
00:04:07.150 --> 00:04:08.109
Get the cages open!

27
00:04:08.193 --> 00:04:09.611
No! No! No!

28
00:04:09.694 --> 00:04:11.529
Listen. you sick bastard.

29
00:04:11.613 --> 00:04:12.906
We're going. and we're taking...

30
00:04:12.989 --> 00:04:13.907
your torture victims with us.

31
00:04:13.990 --> 00:04:15.617
Woman: We're gonna
get you out of here.

32
00:04:15.700 --> 00:04:17.660
Listen. the animals are contagious.

33
00:04:17.744 --> 00:04:19.621
The infection is
in their blood and saliva.

34
00:04:19.704 --> 00:04:21.122
One bite—Stop!

35
00:04:21.206 --> 00:04:22.874
Stop!
You've no idea—

36
00:04:24.709 --> 00:04:25.627
Aah!

37
00:04:25.710 --> 00:04:27.295
Researcher: No!

38
00:04:29.047 --> 00:04:32.217
Get it off!
Oh. God! Help me!

39
00:04:37.222 --> 00:04:39.766
Get it off!
Get it off!

40
00:04:42.644 --> 00:04:43.895
<i>I'm burning!</i>

41
00:04:43.978 --> 00:04:44.896
What the fuck is
the matter with her?!

42
00:04:44.979 --> 00:04:46.606
We have to kill her!

43
00:04:48.733 --> 00:04:50.985
Aah! Oh. my God!

44
00:04:51.069 --> 00:04:52.695
Aah!

45
00:04:54.489 --> 00:04:55.824
What's the matter with her?!

46
00:04:55.907 --> 00:04:57.450
We have to kill her now!

47
00:05:01.079 --> 00:05:02.580
Researcher: Oh. God.

48
00:06:32.754 --> 00:06:34.505
Aah.

49
00:06:51.022 --> 00:06:53.274
Hello?

50
00:07:31.229 --> 00:07:33.064
Hello?

51
00:07:51.249 --> 00:07:53.084
Hello?!

52
00:09:34.769 --> 00:09:37.146
Hello?!

53
00:10:02.547 --> 00:10:04.924
Hello?!

54
00:14:56.507 --> 00:14:57.508
Hello?

55
00:15:06.517 --> 00:15:08.602
Hello?

56
00:15:22.700 --> 00:15:23.742
Father?

57
00:15:31.709 --> 00:15:33.335
Father. are you okay?

58
00:15:40.968 --> 00:15:42.595
Oh. I shouldn't have done that.

59
00:15:43.846 --> 00:15:46.432
I shouldn't have done that.

60
00:15:46.515 --> 00:15:47.766
Shit!

61
00:16:15.252 --> 00:16:17.588
- Over here!
- Move it!

62
00:16:20.382 --> 00:16:22.009
Over here!

63
00:16:22.092 --> 00:16:23.928
Come on!

64
00:16:28.599 --> 00:16:30.184
Burn!

65
00:16:30.267 --> 00:16:32.186
Come on!

66
00:16:35.356 --> 00:16:37.107
Go! Go! Go!

67
00:16:43.072 --> 00:16:43.989
Keep going!

68
00:16:44.073 --> 00:16:45.282
What the fuck is going on?

69
00:16:45.366 --> 00:16:46.700
Just shut up!

70
00:16:56.001 --> 00:16:57.795
Who are those people?

71
00:17:16.981 --> 00:17:18.732
Wha-hoo!

72
00:17:25.030 --> 00:17:26.699
Let's go. Let's go!

73
00:17:26.782 --> 00:17:28.158
Please tell me what
the fuck is going on.

74
00:17:28.242 --> 00:17:29.702
Just move!

75
00:17:37.126 --> 00:17:38.502
Come on!

76
00:17:58.647 --> 00:18:01.567
A man walks into
a bar with a giraffe.

77
00:18:01.650 --> 00:18:05.070
They each get pissed.
The giraffe falls over.

78
00:18:05.154 --> 00:18:08.115
The man goes to leave.
The barman says. “Oi...

79
00:18:08.198 --> 00:18:10.618
you can't leave that lyin' there.”

80
00:18:10.701 --> 00:18:13.579
He says. “No. it's not a lion.

81
00:18:13.662 --> 00:18:16.790
It's a giraffe.”

82
00:18:23.005 --> 00:18:25.341
He's completely humorless.

83
00:18:25.424 --> 00:18:27.718
You two should get on
like a house on fire.

84
00:18:29.470 --> 00:18:33.474
So. who are you?

85
00:18:33.557 --> 00:18:34.600
Well. you're from a hospital. yeah?

86
00:18:34.683 --> 00:18:35.809
You’re a doctor.

87
00:18:35.893 --> 00:18:37.936
He's not a doctor.
He's a patient.

88
00:18:38.020 --> 00:18:40.064
Look. I'm a bicycle courier.

89
00:18:42.566 --> 00:18:46.487
I was riding a package
from. uh. Farringdon...

90
00:18:46.570 --> 00:18:49.615
to Shaftesbury Avenue
when a car cut across me.

91
00:18:49.698 --> 00:18:51.575
And then I wake up
today in hospital.

92
00:18:51.659 --> 00:18:53.661
I wake up. and I'm—

93
00:18:53.744 --> 00:18:55.579
I'm hallucinating. or I'm-

94
00:18:56.872 --> 00:18:58.415
What's your name?

95
00:18:58.499 --> 00:19:00.751
Jim.

96
00:19:02.002 --> 00:19:05.422
I'm Mark.
This is Selena.

97
00:19:08.926 --> 00:19:11.261
Okay. Jim...

98
00:19:16.392 --> 00:19:17.810
I've got some bad news.

99
00:19:19.311 --> 00:19:21.689
It started as rioting...

100
00:19:21.772 --> 00:19:23.357
and right from the beginning...

101
00:19:23.440 --> 00:19:25.401
you knew this was different...

102
00:19:25.484 --> 00:19:26.485
because it was happening...

103
00:19:26.568 --> 00:19:30.197
in small villages. market towns.

104
00:19:30.280 --> 00:19:33.158
And then it wasn't
on the TV anymore.

105
00:19:33.242 --> 00:19:35.035
It was in the street outside...

106
00:19:35.119 --> 00:19:37.204
it was coming through your windows.

107
00:19:37.287 --> 00:19:41.458
It was a virus. an infection.

108
00:19:41.542 --> 00:19:44.545
You didn't need a doctor
to tell you that.

109
00:19:44.628 --> 00:19:46.880
It was the blood.

110
00:19:46.964 --> 00:19:50.467
Or something in the blood.

111
00:19:50.551 --> 00:19:53.053
By the time they tried
to evacuate the cities...

112
00:19:53.137 --> 00:19:56.098
it was already too late.

113
00:19:56.181 --> 00:19:58.559
The infection was everywhere.

114
00:19:58.642 --> 00:20:02.229
The army blockades were overrun.

115
00:20:02.312 --> 00:20:05.899
And that's when the exodus started.

116
00:20:07.693 --> 00:20:08.902
The day before the TV...

117
00:20:08.986 --> 00:20:10.404
and radio stopped broadcasting...

118
00:20:10.487 --> 00:20:11.739
there were reports of infection...

119
00:20:11.822 --> 00:20:13.741
in Paris and New York.

120
00:20:16.201 --> 00:20:18.996
You didn't hear
anything more after that.

121
00:20:22.499 --> 00:20:23.417
What about the government?

122
00:20:23.500 --> 00:20:24.418
What are they doing?

123
00:20:24.501 --> 00:20:25.794
There's no government.

124
00:20:25.878 --> 00:20:27.045
Of course there's a government.

125
00:20:27.129 --> 00:20:29.298
There's always a government.

126
00:20:29.381 --> 00:20:31.759
They're in a bunker or a plane.

127
00:20:31.842 --> 00:20:33.135
No. there's no government...

128
00:20:33.218 --> 00:20:34.553
no police...

129
00:20:34.636 --> 00:20:36.430
no army...

130
00:20:37.931 --> 00:20:40.976
no TV. no radio. no electricity.

131
00:20:41.059 --> 00:20:43.103
You're the first
uninfected person...

132
00:20:43.187 --> 00:20:45.147
we've seen in 6 days.

133
00:20:46.648 --> 00:20:47.566
Where's your family?

134
00:20:48.942 --> 00:20:52.029
They're dead. like Selena's...

135
00:20:52.112 --> 00:20:53.864
yours will be dead. too.

136
00:20:55.365 --> 00:20:56.617
No.

137
00:21:04.208 --> 00:21:05.125
Look. I have to find them.

138
00:21:05.209 --> 00:21:06.335
They live in Deptford.

139
00:21:06.418 --> 00:21:08.086
I can walk it. okay?

140
00:21:08.170 --> 00:21:09.922
What. you'll go and come back. yeah?

141
00:21:10.005 --> 00:21:12.800
Get the fucking—Fuck!

142
00:21:12.883 --> 00:21:14.635
-You won't!
- Yes!

143
00:21:14.718 --> 00:21:16.637
No one ever comes back.

144
00:21:22.476 --> 00:21:25.771
So. lesson one;

145
00:21:25.854 --> 00:21:27.272
You never go anywhere alone...

146
00:21:27.356 --> 00:21:30.025
unless you've got no choice.

147
00:21:30.108 --> 00:21:34.112
And lesson 2: Only
travel during daylight...

148
00:21:34.196 --> 00:21:35.697
unless you've got no choice.

149
00:21:38.951 --> 00:21:40.661
We'll take you tomorrow.

150
00:21:40.744 --> 00:21:43.455
We'll all go and find
your dead parents together. okay?

151
00:21:45.249 --> 00:21:46.875
Eat.

152
00:21:59.221 --> 00:22:00.597
Mark: If you want to slow down...

153
00:22:00.681 --> 00:22:02.099
you'll have to say.

154
00:22:28.876 --> 00:22:30.210
Selena: If there's
anyone in there who is—

155
00:22:30.294 --> 00:22:31.211
Jim: I understand.

156
00:22:31.295 --> 00:22:32.212
Anyone.

157
00:22:32.296 --> 00:22:33.213
I understand.

158
00:22:34.464 --> 00:22:36.425
Mark: Okay.

159
00:23:18.175 --> 00:23:20.636
Jim.

160
00:23:20.719 --> 00:23:22.638
Wait. Jim.

161
00:24:46.805 --> 00:24:49.057
They died peacefully.

162
00:24:49.141 --> 00:24:50.642
You should be grateful.

163
00:24:50.726 --> 00:24:52.185
I'm not grateful.

164
00:24:54.438 --> 00:24:57.107
Mark: My. um...

165
00:24:57.190 --> 00:24:59.735
parents and my sisters...

166
00:24:59.818 --> 00:25:03.989
we went to Paddington Station...

167
00:25:04.072 --> 00:25:05.907
hoping maybe we
could get on a plane...

168
00:25:05.991 --> 00:25:09.536
maybe we could buy
our way onto a plane.

169
00:25:09.619 --> 00:25:12.831
I remember my dad
had all this cash...

170
00:25:12.914 --> 00:25:16.835
even though cash
was completely useless.

171
00:25:16.918 --> 00:25:18.962
About 20.000 other people...

172
00:25:19.046 --> 00:25:21.131
had the same idea.

173
00:25:23.008 --> 00:25:25.719
The crowd was surging.

174
00:25:25.802 --> 00:25:30.182
I lost my grip on my sister's hand.

175
00:25:30.265 --> 00:25:34.686
I remember the ground was soft.

176
00:25:34.770 --> 00:25:36.897
I looked down. and I was standing...

177
00:25:36.980 --> 00:25:40.233
on all these people.
like a carpet...

178
00:25:40.317 --> 00:25:42.152
people who had fallen.

179
00:25:42.235 --> 00:25:44.279
And somewhere in the crowd...

180
00:25:44.362 --> 00:25:46.907
there were infected.
It spread fast.

181
00:25:46.990 --> 00:25:48.909
No one could run.

182
00:25:48.992 --> 00:25:52.079
All you could do was climb...

183
00:25:52.162 --> 00:25:54.581
climb over more people.
So I did that...

184
00:25:54.664 --> 00:25:58.376
I climbed. and I got up
on top of this kiosk.

185
00:26:00.504 --> 00:26:01.546
Looking down. you couldn't tell...

186
00:26:01.630 --> 00:26:03.090
which faces were infected...

187
00:26:03.173 --> 00:26:04.925
and which weren't.

188
00:26:05.008 --> 00:26:06.676
Then I saw my dad...

189
00:26:06.760 --> 00:26:11.264
not my mum or my sister. my dad.

190
00:26:13.266 --> 00:26:16.186
His face.

191
00:26:19.356 --> 00:26:21.900
Selena's right.

192
00:26:21.983 --> 00:26:23.151
You should be grateful.

193
00:26:23.235 --> 00:26:24.152
We don't have time...

194
00:26:24.236 --> 00:26:26.071
to get back to the shop before dark.

195
00:26:26.154 --> 00:26:27.864
We should stay here tonight.

196
00:26:31.535 --> 00:26:33.161
My room is up at the top.
You two can have that.

197
00:26:33.245 --> 00:26:34.162
I'll stay here.

198
00:26:34.246 --> 00:26:35.831
No. we'll all sleep
in the same room.

199
00:26:35.914 --> 00:26:37.374
It's safer.

200
00:27:48.737 --> 00:27:49.779
Tape: It was recorded...

201
00:27:49.863 --> 00:27:51.907
at the Buxton Summer
Music Festival last July...

202
00:27:51.990 --> 00:27:54.618
and it's presented
by Petrov Trelawny.

203
00:27:57.162 --> 00:27:58.121
Jim.

204
00:28:08.590 --> 00:28:09.507
Ah. you're back.

205
00:28:09.591 --> 00:28:10.508
Yeah.

206
00:28:16.848 --> 00:28:17.766
How was it?

207
00:28:17.849 --> 00:28:19.517
Fine.

208
00:28:19.601 --> 00:28:22.020
Give me a drink of that. will you?

209
00:28:22.103 --> 00:28:23.521
It’s empty.

210
00:28:23.605 --> 00:28:24.522
Ah.

211
00:28:26.358 --> 00:28:27.275
Here.

212
00:28:27.359 --> 00:28:29.152
Right.

213
00:28:30.820 --> 00:28:33.323
Father: I'll start
working on them. then.

214
00:28:39.829 --> 00:28:42.290
Mark: Fight! Fight!

215
00:28:42.374 --> 00:28:43.583
Selena!

216
00:28:59.015 --> 00:29:00.684
Selena: It's clear.

217
00:29:06.356 --> 00:29:07.607
That's Mr. Bridges.

218
00:29:07.691 --> 00:29:09.025
Were you bitten?

219
00:29:09.109 --> 00:29:11.111
That's his daughter.

220
00:29:11.194 --> 00:29:12.112
They live 4 doors down.

221
00:29:12.195 --> 00:29:13.405
Were you bitten?

222
00:29:13.488 --> 00:29:15.282
No.

223
00:29:15.365 --> 00:29:17.367
Did any of the blood
get in your mouth?

224
00:29:18.576 --> 00:29:20.036
No.

225
00:29:24.082 --> 00:29:25.041
Mark?

226
00:29:28.086 --> 00:29:29.045
Wait.

227
00:29:52.068 --> 00:29:53.570
Get that cleaned off.

228
00:29:55.697 --> 00:29:57.240
Do you have any clothes here?

229
00:29:59.117 --> 00:30:01.619
Um. —yes.

230
00:30:01.703 --> 00:30:02.996
Then get them and get dressed.

231
00:30:03.079 --> 00:30:04.331
We have to leave now.

232
00:30:04.414 --> 00:30:07.250
More infected will be coming.

233
00:30:07.334 --> 00:30:09.044
They always do.

234
00:30:37.322 --> 00:30:38.656
Jim: How did you know?

235
00:30:38.740 --> 00:30:40.700
I mean. how did you know
he was infected?

236
00:30:40.784 --> 00:30:41.701
Selena: The blood.

237
00:30:41.785 --> 00:30:43.078
Yeah. but there
was blood everywhere.

238
00:30:43.161 --> 00:30:44.746
It was on me.
It was on you.

239
00:30:44.829 --> 00:30:46.539
I didn't know he was infected. okay?

240
00:30:46.623 --> 00:30:48.792
He knew.
I could see it in his face.

241
00:30:50.085 --> 00:30:51.628
Look. if someone gets infected...

242
00:30:51.711 --> 00:30:54.005
you've got between
10 and 20 seconds to kill them.

243
00:30:54.089 --> 00:30:56.674
It might be your brother
or your sister...

244
00:30:56.758 --> 00:30:57.759
or your oldest friend.

245
00:30:57.842 --> 00:30:59.719
It makes no difference.

246
00:30:59.803 --> 00:31:00.887
And just so you know
where you stand...

247
00:31:00.970 --> 00:31:03.598
if it happens to you.
I'll do it in a heartbeat.

248
00:31:05.517 --> 00:31:08.019
He was full of plans.

249
00:31:08.103 --> 00:31:09.396
Have you got any plans. Jim?

250
00:31:09.479 --> 00:31:11.481
Do you want us to find
a cure and save the world...

251
00:31:11.564 --> 00:31:13.817
or just fall in love and fuck?

252
00:31:13.900 --> 00:31:15.568
Plans are pointless.

253
00:31:16.778 --> 00:31:19.072
Staying alive's as good as it gets.

254
00:31:20.949 --> 00:31:22.742
Hey. hey. hey. hey. hey. hey.

255
00:31:22.826 --> 00:31:23.743
what’s that?

256
00:31:30.500 --> 00:31:31.418
Selena: Let's go.

257
00:32:16.754 --> 00:32:19.382
What is it about tower blocks...

258
00:32:19.466 --> 00:32:21.426
and shopping trolleys. huh?

259
00:32:21.509 --> 00:32:23.636
Stop talking.
It's a long way up.

260
00:32:33.521 --> 00:32:35.273
Selena: Do you need a break?

261
00:32:35.356 --> 00:32:36.274
No.

262
00:32:37.692 --> 00:32:39.068
-You?
- No.

263
00:32:41.863 --> 00:32:45.408
Now I do need a break...
by the way.

264
00:32:54.334 --> 00:32:56.503
What's up?

265
00:32:56.586 --> 00:32:57.921
Nothin'.

266
00:33:01.090 --> 00:33:02.300
Got a headache.

267
00:33:02.383 --> 00:33:03.510
Bad?

268
00:33:03.593 --> 00:33:04.552
Yeah. it’s pretty bad.

269
00:33:04.636 --> 00:33:06.304
Well. why didn't you
say something before?

270
00:33:06.387 --> 00:33:08.264
Well. because I didn't think
you'd give a shit.

271
00:33:10.767 --> 00:33:12.352
You've got no fat on you...

272
00:33:12.435 --> 00:33:14.938
and all you've
had to eat is sugar...

273
00:33:15.021 --> 00:33:16.689
so you're crashing.

274
00:33:16.773 --> 00:33:18.149
Unfortunately. there isn't a lot...

275
00:33:18.233 --> 00:33:19.275
we can do about that...

276
00:33:19.359 --> 00:33:21.069
except pump you
full of painkillers...

277
00:33:21.152 --> 00:33:22.070
and give you more sugar.

278
00:33:22.153 --> 00:33:28.201
As for sugar. Pepsi or Lilt?

279
00:33:28.284 --> 00:33:30.328
Do you have any Tango?

280
00:33:30.411 --> 00:33:33.248
Actually. I did have
a can of Tango somewhere.

281
00:33:34.332 --> 00:33:36.793
Quiet! That's an infected.

282
00:33:47.220 --> 00:33:48.972
Oh. no. They're in. Move!

283
00:33:52.100 --> 00:33:53.142
Jim: Wait. Selena!

284
00:33:55.436 --> 00:33:56.896
Wait for me. please!

285
00:33:56.980 --> 00:33:58.898
Wait. Selena!

286
00:33:58.982 --> 00:34:01.859
Please wait for me!

287
00:34:01.943 --> 00:34:03.027
- Selena!
- Come on!

288
00:34:03.111 --> 00:34:04.237
- Wait!
- Run!

289
00:34:04.320 --> 00:34:07.699
Wait. for fuck's sake!

290
00:34:07.782 --> 00:34:09.158
Selena!

291
00:34:09.242 --> 00:34:10.410
Aah!

292
00:34:12.203 --> 00:34:14.163
Down the corridor. flat 157!

293
00:34:14.247 --> 00:34:15.540
Move!

294
00:34:15.623 --> 00:34:16.791
Jim: Thank you!
Thank you!

295
00:34:29.846 --> 00:34:31.014
Open the door!

296
00:34:37.812 --> 00:34:39.355
Open the door!

297
00:34:43.484 --> 00:34:44.986
Open up!

298
00:34:45.069 --> 00:34:46.863
Where's Dad?
What?!

299
00:34:50.700 --> 00:34:51.576
Open the fucking door!

300
00:34:51.659 --> 00:34:52.952
Where's Dad?!

301
00:34:53.036 --> 00:34:54.120
Fucking open the door!

302
00:34:54.203 --> 00:34:56.039
Hannah. let them inside.

303
00:35:03.463 --> 00:35:05.048
Go In.

304
00:35:05.131 --> 00:35:06.507
Go In.

305
00:35:24.233 --> 00:35:26.361
So. I'm Frank. anyway.

306
00:35:26.444 --> 00:35:27.403
Jim.

307
00:35:29.530 --> 00:35:30.907
Selena.

308
00:35:30.990 --> 00:35:32.575
Selena. good to meet you.

309
00:35:32.659 --> 00:35:34.410
This is my daughter Hannah.

310
00:35:34.494 --> 00:35:36.579
Come on. sweetheart.
Say hello.

311
00:35:38.831 --> 00:35:39.749
Come on.

312
00:35:41.668 --> 00:35:43.670
So—

313
00:35:43.753 --> 00:35:45.505
This is great.
It's just great.

314
00:35:47.882 --> 00:35:50.343
Calls for a celebration. I'd say.

315
00:35:50.426 --> 00:35:51.969
Why don't you all sit down...

316
00:35:52.053 --> 00:35:55.848
and. uh. Hannah. what
have we got to offer?

317
00:35:55.932 --> 00:35:58.518
We’ve got Mum’s crème de menthe.

318
00:35:58.601 --> 00:36:00.812
Great.
Her crème de menthe.

319
00:36:00.895 --> 00:36:02.772
Aye.

320
00:36:02.855 --> 00:36:04.315
Look. sit. please.

321
00:36:04.399 --> 00:36:05.942
Get comfortable.

322
00:36:09.779 --> 00:36:11.489
Frank: Where are
the bloody glasses?!

323
00:36:11.572 --> 00:36:12.907
Middle cupboard.

324
00:36:12.990 --> 00:36:15.868
No. the good ones.
It's a celebration.

325
00:36:15.952 --> 00:36:16.869
Top cupboard.

326
00:36:16.953 --> 00:36:19.622
So...50. this is your place?

327
00:36:22.667 --> 00:36:24.210
It's nice.

328
00:36:32.176 --> 00:36:33.136
Yeah.

329
00:36:37.098 --> 00:36:38.474
Now...

330
00:36:38.558 --> 00:36:41.269
I know it isn't much.
but. well. cheers.

331
00:36:41.352 --> 00:36:43.479
Cheers.

332
00:37:05.001 --> 00:37:06.252
You okay in there. Jim?

333
00:37:08.045 --> 00:37:09.005
Yeah.

334
00:37:10.506 --> 00:37:12.842
Sorry we couldn't spare the water.

335
00:37:12.925 --> 00:37:13.926
Same with the toilet.

336
00:37:14.010 --> 00:37:16.053
The. um. flush doesn't work.

337
00:37:17.680 --> 00:37:19.348
Afraid you'll have
to use the bucket.

338
00:37:26.397 --> 00:37:29.275
Have to empty it
each morning. you know.

339
00:37:29.358 --> 00:37:30.860
Just chuck it over the balcony.

340
00:37:30.943 --> 00:37:32.278
No mod cons here.

341
00:37:32.361 --> 00:37:34.238
Yeah. It's fine.

342
00:37:34.322 --> 00:37:35.615
Yeah. alright. listen...

343
00:37:35.698 --> 00:37:37.366
it's late.
I'm gonna turn in.

344
00:37:38.951 --> 00:37:42.830
We have a spare room...

345
00:37:42.914 --> 00:37:44.290
in there.

346
00:37:44.373 --> 00:37:46.375
Are you and Selena—

347
00:37:47.627 --> 00:37:49.420
Oh. no. No. no. no.

348
00:37:49.504 --> 00:37:53.716
Um. no. I'll take
the living room. It's fine.

349
00:37:53.800 --> 00:37:54.717
Right.

350
00:37:56.552 --> 00:37:57.970
Oh. no. I mean. yeah.

351
00:37:59.722 --> 00:38:02.099
Yeah. so. um. alright.

352
00:38:02.183 --> 00:38:03.851
Okay. good night. then. anyway.

353
00:38:03.935 --> 00:38:05.561
Yeah. good night. Frank.

354
00:38:19.742 --> 00:38:21.869
Very spruce.

355
00:38:21.953 --> 00:38:24.580
Yeah...
very shredded.

356
00:38:24.664 --> 00:38:25.581
Yeah.

357
00:38:29.919 --> 00:38:32.046
So what do you make of them?

358
00:38:32.129 --> 00:38:35.049
Well. they're desperate.

359
00:38:35.132 --> 00:38:37.051
Probably need us
more than we need them.

360
00:38:39.554 --> 00:38:41.556
I think they're good people.

361
00:38:44.600 --> 00:38:45.685
Good people?

362
00:38:45.768 --> 00:38:46.894
Yeah.

363
00:38:49.438 --> 00:38:50.356
Well. that's nice...

364
00:38:50.439 --> 00:38:51.440
but you should be more concerned...

365
00:38:51.524 --> 00:38:54.068
about whether
they're gonna slow you down.

366
00:38:54.151 --> 00:38:56.404
Right. because if
they slowed you down—

367
00:38:56.487 --> 00:38:57.905
I'd leave them behind.

368
00:38:57.989 --> 00:38:59.866
- In a heartbeat.
- Yeah.

369
00:38:59.949 --> 00:39:02.285
I wouldn't.

370
00:39:02.368 --> 00:39:04.954
Then you're gonna wind up
getting yourself killed.

371
00:39:14.297 --> 00:39:15.423
I'm gonna get some sleep.

372
00:39:19.010 --> 00:39:21.470
Selena...

373
00:39:21.554 --> 00:39:23.389
you think I don't get it...

374
00:39:23.472 --> 00:39:25.266
but. um. I do get it.

375
00:39:27.310 --> 00:39:28.895
And I know I'd be dead already...

376
00:39:28.978 --> 00:39:31.063
if I hadn't met you.

377
00:39:31.147 --> 00:39:32.106
Sure.

378
00:39:33.274 --> 00:39:34.817
No. look...

379
00:39:36.694 --> 00:39:39.030
I mean thank you.

380
00:39:42.491 --> 00:39:44.660
And I mean sure.

381
00:39:44.744 --> 00:39:46.412
Good night. Jim.

382
00:39:46.495 --> 00:39:48.331
Good night.

383
00:40:03.262 --> 00:40:04.931
Frank: We lost water pressure
3 weeks ago.

384
00:40:05.014 --> 00:40:06.349
For a while.
I thought we'd be okay...

385
00:40:06.432 --> 00:40:07.767
with the water in the other flats...

386
00:40:07.850 --> 00:40:09.185
cisterns. and tanks...

387
00:40:09.268 --> 00:40:12.021
but it vanishes so quick.
you wouldn't believe.

388
00:40:16.067 --> 00:40:19.403
You drink it.
It evaporates...

389
00:40:19.487 --> 00:40:21.030
turns stagnant.

390
00:40:24.116 --> 00:40:25.493
They're all empty.

391
00:40:27.578 --> 00:40:29.288
Hasn't rained in 10 days.

392
00:40:29.372 --> 00:40:30.957
You can set up a plastic sheet...

393
00:40:31.040 --> 00:40:32.500
to catch dew and condensation...

394
00:40:32.583 --> 00:40:33.918
trap it somehow.

395
00:40:34.001 --> 00:40:38.089
I saw it on TV once.
but I can't make it work.

396
00:40:38.172 --> 00:40:41.676
You'd never think it...

397
00:40:41.759 --> 00:40:43.886
needing rain so badly.

398
00:40:46.180 --> 00:40:48.808
Not in fucking England.

399
00:40:53.521 --> 00:40:57.024
Jim. we're not gonna
be able to stay here.

400
00:41:05.741 --> 00:41:07.743
Selena: There haven't been
any broadcasts for weeks.

401
00:41:07.827 --> 00:41:08.995
Just listen.

402
00:41:09.078 --> 00:41:10.663
Man On Radio: ...Salvation is here.

403
00:41:10.746 --> 00:41:13.874
The answer to infection is here.

404
00:41:13.958 --> 00:41:17.003
If you can hear this.
you're not alone.

405
00:41:17.086 --> 00:41:18.754
There are others like you.

406
00:41:18.838 --> 00:41:22.008
There are fighters. other survivors.

407
00:41:22.091 --> 00:41:23.926
We are soldiers. and we are armed.

408
00:41:24.010 --> 00:41:27.471
Selena: Oh. my God. Soldiers.

409
00:41:27.555 --> 00:41:28.639
Quiet. There's more.

410
00:41:28.723 --> 00:41:30.182
Man On Radio: Our location
is the 42nd Blockade...

411
00:41:30.266 --> 00:41:35.646
the M602. 27 miles
northeast of Manchester.

412
00:41:35.730 --> 00:41:37.773
You must find us.
Salvation is—

413
00:41:37.857 --> 00:41:39.275
Then it just repeats.

414
00:41:39.358 --> 00:41:40.985
What. so it's a recording?

415
00:41:41.068 --> 00:41:42.028
Yeah. it's a recording...

416
00:41:42.111 --> 00:41:44.488
but this is where
it's telling us to go.

417
00:41:44.572 --> 00:41:47.199
Just there.

418
00:41:48.951 --> 00:41:49.910
The way things are...

419
00:41:49.994 --> 00:41:52.955
we might need
2. 3 days to get up there.

420
00:41:53.039 --> 00:41:55.124
Um. "we"?

421
00:41:59.336 --> 00:42:00.755
Sound carries in this flat.

422
00:42:00.838 --> 00:42:02.298
You know. jerry-built. I suppose.

423
00:42:02.381 --> 00:42:04.383
Me and Hannah do need you...

424
00:42:04.467 --> 00:42:05.509
more than you need us.

425
00:42:05.593 --> 00:42:06.635
Look. I didn't—

426
00:42:06.719 --> 00:42:08.596
That's okay.
It's the truth.

427
00:42:08.679 --> 00:42:09.597
I can't leave the block...

428
00:42:09.680 --> 00:42:11.057
if it's just the two of us.

429
00:42:11.140 --> 00:42:12.475
Something might happen to me.

430
00:42:12.558 --> 00:42:14.310
Hannah'd be alone.
I couldn't risk it...

431
00:42:15.352 --> 00:42:17.146
but with other people—

432
00:42:17.229 --> 00:42:19.065
If it's a recording.
for all we know...

433
00:42:19.148 --> 00:42:21.442
the soldiers who made it are dead.

434
00:42:21.525 --> 00:42:22.568
It's possible. yeah.

435
00:42:22.651 --> 00:42:24.945
And that stuff
about the answer to infection...

436
00:42:25.029 --> 00:42:27.198
I mean. there is no answer
to infection.

437
00:42:27.281 --> 00:42:29.200
It's already done pretty much
all the damage it can.

438
00:42:29.283 --> 00:42:30.201
Maybe they have a cure.

439
00:42:30.284 --> 00:42:32.661
Maybe they've got nothing at all.

440
00:42:32.745 --> 00:42:34.455
Well. the only way to
find out is to reach them!

441
00:42:34.538 --> 00:42:36.582
We could die trying. Frank!

442
00:42:38.334 --> 00:42:40.669
Or die here...

443
00:42:40.753 --> 00:42:44.006
and anyway. it isn't
true what Dad said.

444
00:42:44.090 --> 00:42:46.759
You need us just the
same as we need you.

445
00:42:48.302 --> 00:42:50.137
We need each other...

446
00:42:50.221 --> 00:42:52.348
and we'll never be
safe in the cities.

447
00:42:52.431 --> 00:42:53.682
The soldiers could keep us safe.

448
00:42:55.601 --> 00:42:58.979
So we have to try and get there.

449
00:42:59.063 --> 00:43:01.107
Get there how?

450
00:43:12.201 --> 00:43:13.869
Just so you know...

451
00:43:13.953 --> 00:43:16.205
I don't take checks or credit cards.

452
00:43:44.400 --> 00:43:45.651
Frank: What do you think?

453
00:43:45.734 --> 00:43:46.735
Well. it's the most direct route...

454
00:43:46.819 --> 00:43:47.862
to the other side of the river.

455
00:43:47.945 --> 00:43:49.071
No. no. no. then we should take...

456
00:43:49.155 --> 00:43:50.114
the indirect route...

457
00:43:50.197 --> 00:43:51.574
the one that's in broad daylight...

458
00:43:51.657 --> 00:43:53.159
and that's not underground.

459
00:43:53.242 --> 00:43:54.451
Frank: Let's just get it done.

460
00:44:08.299 --> 00:44:10.426
Jim: No. no.

461
00:44:10.509 --> 00:44:13.220
No. see. this is a really shit idea.

462
00:44:13.304 --> 00:44:14.680
You know why?

463
00:44:14.763 --> 00:44:17.516
Because it's really
obviously a shit idea.

464
00:44:17.600 --> 00:44:19.727
So. we're just gonna
drive into a tunnel...

465
00:44:19.810 --> 00:44:22.313
full of fuckin' smashed
cars and broken glass.

466
00:44:22.396 --> 00:44:24.982
It's just really fucking
obviously a shit idea!

467
00:44:25.065 --> 00:44:26.108
Hold on!

468
00:44:36.493 --> 00:44:37.620
Hannah: Dad!

469
00:44:40.331 --> 00:44:41.624
- Aah!
- Whoa!

470
00:44:57.431 --> 00:44:58.390
Fuck!

471
00:45:00.142 --> 00:45:02.645
World's worst place
to get a flat. huh?

472
00:45:02.728 --> 00:45:03.854
Agreed.

473
00:45:03.938 --> 00:45:05.397
I think we better do this quick.

474
00:45:08.984 --> 00:45:11.111
Frank: I've got the wheel.
You’re on the jack.

475
00:45:25.751 --> 00:45:27.127
Hey. did you hear that?
Hey. hey.

476
00:45:27.211 --> 00:45:29.296
Did you hear that?

477
00:45:29.380 --> 00:45:30.339
Hear what?

478
00:45:31.882 --> 00:45:33.467
Hannah: Right. I've done it.

479
00:45:35.552 --> 00:45:37.513
Dad?

480
00:45:41.350 --> 00:45:43.060
Jim: Jesus Christ!

481
00:45:43.143 --> 00:45:46.021
Oh. no!
Fucking rats!

482
00:45:46.105 --> 00:45:47.147
Aah!

483
00:45:47.231 --> 00:45:49.191
Frank: Come on. Hannah. out! Out!

484
00:45:56.573 --> 00:45:59.618
They're running from the infected.

485
00:45:59.702 --> 00:46:01.453
Move it!

486
00:46:01.537 --> 00:46:02.413
Frank: Forget the jack. Hannah!

487
00:46:02.496 --> 00:46:03.455
Selena: Don't look at them!

488
00:46:03.539 --> 00:46:04.415
Frank: There's no time!
Forget the jack!

489
00:46:04.498 --> 00:46:05.624
Just lift. everyone!

490
00:46:05.708 --> 00:46:06.667
Grab hold!

491
00:46:09.128 --> 00:46:11.213
Lift!

492
00:46:13.215 --> 00:46:14.800
Lift! Lift!

493
00:46:14.883 --> 00:46:17.678
Selena: Don't look at them!
Don't look at them!

494
00:46:17.761 --> 00:46:20.472
Jim: I can see them!
They're coming! Aah!

495
00:46:26.020 --> 00:46:27.438
Selena; Come on. Hannah!

496
00:46:27.521 --> 00:46:28.856
Put it on!

497
00:46:28.939 --> 00:46:30.190
Hannah: Almost!

498
00:46:31.400 --> 00:46:32.776
Jim: Get the tire on. Hannah!

499
00:46:32.860 --> 00:46:34.236
- Alright!
- Get it on. Hannah!

500
00:46:39.116 --> 00:46:42.369
Hannah: 3...2...1.
Drop it!

501
00:46:44.455 --> 00:46:46.707
Jim: Inside. everyone!
Inside!

502
00:46:46.790 --> 00:46:50.044
Selena; Get in the cab!
Get in the cab!

503
00:46:50.127 --> 00:46:51.587
Jim: Get in the fucking cab!

504
00:46:51.670 --> 00:46:53.213
Selena: Frank. drive!

505
00:46:54.673 --> 00:46:56.550
Hannah: Aah!

506
00:46:56.633 --> 00:46:59.470
Jim: Whoo!

507
00:47:04.224 --> 00:47:07.728
Jim: Bye-bye. you fuckers! Whoo!

508
00:47:14.485 --> 00:47:16.362
Selena: Hey. Frank.
Frank. stop the cab.

509
00:47:39.593 --> 00:47:41.053
Let's shop.

510
00:47:52.731 --> 00:47:54.775
You...

511
00:47:54.858 --> 00:47:56.402
You...

512
00:47:56.485 --> 00:47:57.903
You...

513
00:47:57.986 --> 00:48:00.572
Jim: Has anybody seen any buns?

514
00:48:00.656 --> 00:48:03.909
Mmm. Irradiated.

515
00:48:07.162 --> 00:48:10.499
And don't take anything
that needs to be cooked. okay?

516
00:48:10.582 --> 00:48:11.959
I think you can eat that raw.

517
00:48:12.042 --> 00:48:14.086
Decaffeinated coffee.

518
00:48:14.169 --> 00:48:15.129
Frank: Put that back.

519
00:48:17.339 --> 00:48:19.800
Can't just take any crap.

520
00:48:19.883 --> 00:48:21.677
If I never see
another chocolate bar again...

521
00:48:21.760 --> 00:48:23.554
it will be too soon.

522
00:48:24.972 --> 00:48:27.391
Not counting Terry's
chocolate orange. of course!

523
00:48:27.474 --> 00:48:29.143
There.

524
00:48:29.226 --> 00:48:31.645
Now. single malt. 16-year-old.

525
00:48:31.728 --> 00:48:33.605
Dark. full-flavor.

526
00:48:33.689 --> 00:48:35.816
Warm. but not aggressive.

527
00:48:35.899 --> 00:48:39.153
Peaty aftertaste.

528
00:48:39.236 --> 00:48:40.654
Yeah.

529
00:48:40.737 --> 00:48:43.532
Takes out the fire.
but leaves in the warmth.

530
00:49:01.008 --> 00:49:01.925
Ha ha ha.

531
00:49:38.921 --> 00:49:41.924
Either we do this now.
or we're walking.

532
00:49:48.639 --> 00:49:49.932
Frank: Not you.

533
00:49:53.936 --> 00:49:55.395
Stay close. Jim.

534
00:49:55.479 --> 00:49:56.939
What?

535
00:49:57.022 --> 00:49:57.940
You heard me.

536
00:50:25.050 --> 00:50:26.760
Where are you going?

537
00:50:28.720 --> 00:50:30.722
We've got enough food. Jim.

538
00:50:30.806 --> 00:50:33.141
We don't have any cheeseburgers.

539
00:50:34.351 --> 00:50:36.812
Like going on holidays
with your fuckin' aunt.

540
00:51:16.101 --> 00:51:18.520
Oh. Jesus.

541
00:51:43.962 --> 00:51:45.714
Hello?

542
00:51:59.519 --> 00:52:00.854
I hate you!

543
00:52:10.781 --> 00:52:11.865
Find anything?

544
00:52:14.951 --> 00:52:16.036
Find anything. Jim?

545
00:52:16.119 --> 00:52:17.371
No. Let's get out of here.

546
00:52:17.454 --> 00:52:18.872
Okay. we're done here.

547
00:52:21.958 --> 00:52:22.918
Okay. Hannah!

548
00:52:30.884 --> 00:52:35.263
Steady. Easy. Brake.
Brake! Brake!

549
00:52:42.854 --> 00:52:43.772
Out.

550
00:53:29.192 --> 00:53:30.736
Selena: Mmm!

551
00:53:30.819 --> 00:53:33.780
Oh. my God!

552
00:53:33.864 --> 00:53:36.491
I can. like. taste the vitamin “C.”

553
00:53:37.617 --> 00:53:41.246
Okay. the raisins are still moist.

554
00:53:41.329 --> 00:53:43.874
What did you say?

555
00:53:43.957 --> 00:53:45.250
The raisins. yeah?

556
00:53:45.333 --> 00:53:47.669
They're still moist.

557
00:53:51.339 --> 00:53:52.340
Look over here.

558
00:54:04.728 --> 00:54:06.104
Like a family.

559
00:54:06.188 --> 00:54:09.107
Hannah: Do you think
they're infected?

560
00:54:09.191 --> 00:54:10.108
Frank: No.

561
00:54:14.488 --> 00:54:16.490
They're doing just fine.

562
00:54:22.996 --> 00:54:25.373
Come on. Let's eat!

563
00:54:40.847 --> 00:54:41.932
Jim: Do you know
what I was thinking?

564
00:54:42.015 --> 00:54:43.016
Selena: You were thinking
that you'll never hear...

565
00:54:43.099 --> 00:54:45.393
another piece of
original music ever again.

566
00:54:45.477 --> 00:54:47.479
You'll never read a book...

567
00:54:47.562 --> 00:54:50.732
that hasn't already been written...

568
00:54:50.816 --> 00:54:54.611
or see a film that hasn't
already been shot.

569
00:54:59.032 --> 00:55:02.369
Um. that's what you were thinking.

570
00:55:02.452 --> 00:55:03.411
No.

571
00:55:05.747 --> 00:55:09.042
I was thinking I was wrong.

572
00:55:09.125 --> 00:55:10.085
About what?

573
00:55:12.921 --> 00:55:15.549
All the death...

574
00:55:15.632 --> 00:55:16.758
all the shit.

575
00:55:19.302 --> 00:55:20.554
It doesn't really mean anything...

576
00:55:20.637 --> 00:55:21.972
to Frank and Hannah.
because—

577
00:55:25.100 --> 00:55:26.101
Well. she's got a dad...

578
00:55:26.184 --> 00:55:28.854
and he's got
his daughter. so—

579
00:55:28.937 --> 00:55:30.856
Cheeky monkey.

580
00:55:30.939 --> 00:55:32.148
I was wrong when I said...

581
00:55:32.232 --> 00:55:34.943
that staying alive
is as good as it gets.

582
00:55:38.613 --> 00:55:41.032
You see. that's what I was thinking.

583
00:55:41.116 --> 00:55:43.076
Was it?

584
00:55:43.159 --> 00:55:44.077
MmMmm.

585
00:55:44.160 --> 00:55:45.453
You stole my thought.

586
00:55:50.917 --> 00:55:53.628
Sorry.

587
00:55:53.712 --> 00:55:56.047
That's okay.
You keep it.

588
00:55:58.800 --> 00:55:59.718
Frank: It's getting late.

589
00:55:59.801 --> 00:56:01.678
Think we better stay here
for the night.

590
00:56:18.028 --> 00:56:20.488
Can't sleep.

591
00:56:20.572 --> 00:56:21.489
Me neither.

592
00:56:23.241 --> 00:56:25.702
Jim: Doesn't feel safe. does it?

593
00:56:25.785 --> 00:56:26.703
Outside like this.

594
00:56:28.788 --> 00:56:30.415
I think we're safe enough.

595
00:56:30.498 --> 00:56:34.586
Selena didn't seem
to have any trouble.

596
00:56:34.669 --> 00:56:35.837
Yeah. I noticed that.

597
00:56:37.172 --> 00:56:38.798
Hey. Selena.

598
00:56:38.882 --> 00:56:41.843
What? What is it?

599
00:56:41.927 --> 00:56:43.094
How did you get to sleep?

600
00:56:43.178 --> 00:56:44.512
Oh.

601
00:56:50.518 --> 00:56:51.436
Frank: Bloody hell.

602
00:56:51.519 --> 00:56:52.854
You must have needed...

603
00:56:52.938 --> 00:56:54.272
a hell of a prescription
for that lot.

604
00:56:54.356 --> 00:56:55.941
I didn't need a prescription.

605
00:56:56.024 --> 00:56:57.609
I qualified as a chemist.

606
00:56:58.860 --> 00:57:00.278
Jim: Oh. great. Valium.

607
00:57:01.446 --> 00:57:04.199
Not only will we be able
to get to sleep...

608
00:57:04.282 --> 00:57:06.326
but if we're attacked
in the middle of the night...

609
00:57:06.409 --> 00:57:07.452
we won't even care.

610
00:57:08.001 --> 00:57:08.620
2 each.

611
00:57:08.703 --> 00:57:10.372
No. not for me. thanks.

612
00:57:10.455 --> 00:57:12.457
Hannah: Can I. Dad?

613
00:57:12.540 --> 00:57:14.793
Frank: I don't think so. sweetheart.

614
00:57:14.876 --> 00:57:16.086
Please?

615
00:57:17.212 --> 00:57:18.129
No.

616
00:57:18.213 --> 00:57:19.464
I can't sleep.

617
00:57:22.300 --> 00:57:24.135
Jim: Come on. Frank.

618
00:57:24.219 --> 00:57:26.513
Let her live a little.

619
00:57:26.596 --> 00:57:27.931
Give her half of one.

620
00:57:28.014 --> 00:57:29.641
Jim: Alright.
We're on.

621
00:57:41.361 --> 00:57:42.278
Hannah: Night-night.

622
00:57:44.155 --> 00:57:45.740
Jim: You're a big softie. Frank.

623
00:58:17.272 --> 00:58:19.190
Frank?

624
00:58:19.274 --> 00:58:21.192
Hannah?

625
00:58:21.276 --> 00:58:22.277
Frank?

626
00:58:28.867 --> 00:58:30.076
Hello?

627
00:58:30.160 --> 00:58:32.078
Hello?

628
00:58:32.162 --> 00:58:33.371
Hello?

629
00:58:33.455 --> 00:58:34.873
Hello?

630
00:58:34.956 --> 00:58:35.915
Hello?

631
00:58:44.049 --> 00:58:45.633
Frank: Shh.

632
00:58:47.427 --> 00:58:49.054
You're having a bad dream.
that's all.

633
00:58:52.849 --> 00:58:53.808
Thanks. Dad.

634
00:59:30.261 --> 00:59:32.347
Come on. sleepyhead.

635
00:59:36.768 --> 00:59:38.603
Come on. Babe Ruth.

636
00:59:41.898 --> 00:59:42.857
Frank: Hurry up.

637
00:59:45.693 --> 00:59:46.611
Jim: Oh. no.

638
00:59:46.694 --> 00:59:47.654
Did I miss breakfast?

639
00:59:47.737 --> 00:59:49.114
Selena: You'll sleep
through anything. you.

640
00:59:49.197 --> 00:59:50.198
Jim: Did you have a fry-up?

641
00:59:50.281 --> 00:59:52.784
Frank: Maybe stop
at a pub along the way?

642
00:59:52.867 --> 00:59:53.785
Door.

643
01:00:15.431 --> 01:00:18.601
Man On Radio: ..We can feed you
and we can protect you.

644
01:00:18.685 --> 01:00:21.813
Our location is the 42nd Blockade...

645
01:00:21.896 --> 01:00:26.317
the M602. 27 miles northeast
of Manchester.

646
01:00:26.401 --> 01:00:28.486
You must find us. please.

647
01:00:28.570 --> 01:00:30.613
Salvation is here.

648
01:00:30.697 --> 01:00:33.575
The answer to infection is here.

649
01:00:50.216 --> 01:00:51.467
- Sure?
-Yo.

650
01:01:05.732 --> 01:01:06.900
Must be Manchester.

651
01:01:10.111 --> 01:01:11.654
The whole of Manchester.

652
01:01:11.738 --> 01:01:12.697
The whole city.

653
01:01:15.575 --> 01:01:17.160
No fire crews to put it out.

654
01:02:12.548 --> 01:02:15.176
42nd Blockade.

655
01:02:15.260 --> 01:02:16.177
This is it.

656
01:03:28.791 --> 01:03:30.918
I don't understand. Dad.

657
01:03:31.002 --> 01:03:32.337
Did they leave?

658
01:03:32.420 --> 01:03:33.421
I don't like this.

659
01:03:33.504 --> 01:03:34.589
I think we should go.

660
01:03:34.672 --> 01:03:35.590
No!

661
01:03:42.638 --> 01:03:43.639
Vehicles.

662
01:03:43.723 --> 01:03:44.640
We should check the vehicles.

663
01:03:44.724 --> 01:03:45.641
There has to be something.

664
01:04:05.578 --> 01:04:07.580
Nothing.

665
01:04:07.663 --> 01:04:09.165
Can't believe it.

666
01:04:09.248 --> 01:04:10.166
Selena: Frank.

667
01:04:11.709 --> 01:04:12.960
Frank.

668
01:04:15.963 --> 01:04:16.881
We have to go?

669
01:04:16.964 --> 01:04:17.882
Yeah.

670
01:04:17.965 --> 01:04:19.384
Go fucking where?!

671
01:04:59.257 --> 01:05:00.299
Get out of it.

672
01:05:05.179 --> 01:05:06.097
Get out of it.

673
01:05:25.116 --> 01:05:26.617
Dad. are you alright?

674
01:05:27.827 --> 01:05:28.953
Yeah. I'm fine. sweetheart.

675
01:05:31.289 --> 01:05:33.082
Sorry I lost my temper.

676
01:05:34.167 --> 01:05:36.294
Hannah.

677
01:05:36.377 --> 01:05:38.254
I love you very much.

678
01:05:38.337 --> 01:05:39.714
What?

679
01:05:39.797 --> 01:05:41.466
Keep away from me.

680
01:05:41.549 --> 01:05:43.301
Stay where you are.

681
01:05:43.384 --> 01:05:44.343
- Ow.
- Dad?

682
01:05:44.427 --> 01:05:45.803
- Keep away from me!
- Dad?

683
01:05:45.887 --> 01:05:46.804
Keep away from me!

684
01:05:46.888 --> 01:05:48.306
- Keep away from me!
- Dad!

685
01:05:48.389 --> 01:05:50.308
- Keep away from me!
- Dad!

686
01:05:50.391 --> 01:05:52.643
Keep away!
Keep away!

687
01:05:54.312 --> 01:05:55.229
Hannah: What's wrong?

688
01:05:55.313 --> 01:05:56.814
Dad!

689
01:06:00.401 --> 01:06:02.153
Jim!

690
01:06:02.236 --> 01:06:04.071
Jim. he's infected!

691
01:06:04.155 --> 01:06:05.072
Hannah: No! No!

692
01:06:05.156 --> 01:06:06.324
Selena: Jim!

693
01:06:06.407 --> 01:06:07.492
Jim. kill him!

694
01:06:07.575 --> 01:06:09.827
- Dad!
- Kill him!

695
01:06:09.911 --> 01:06:10.995
Kill him!

696
01:06:19.754 --> 01:06:21.088
Stay away from him!

697
01:06:23.257 --> 01:06:24.967
Keep away from the body!

698
01:06:28.221 --> 01:06:29.472
Dad?

699
01:06:52.453 --> 01:06:55.289
Soldier: 3 survivors—
one male. 2 female.

700
01:06:55.373 --> 01:06:58.709
I repeat. one male. 2 female.

701
01:06:58.793 --> 01:07:01.546
<i>EVANS..</i>

702
01:07:01.629 --> 01:07:02.588
Put the kettle on.

703
01:07:51.887 --> 01:07:53.514
Man: I’m Major Henry West.

704
01:07:55.308 --> 01:07:56.225
Welcome.

705
01:07:56.309 --> 01:07:57.226
Jim.

706
01:07:57.310 --> 01:07:58.227
Hello. Jim.

707
01:07:59.604 --> 01:08:01.272
Hello.

708
01:08:03.524 --> 01:08:05.818
Well. we've got beds
with clean sheets...

709
01:08:05.901 --> 01:08:08.571
and a boiler
that produces hot water...

710
01:08:08.654 --> 01:08:10.948
so you can all have a shower.

711
01:08:11.032 --> 01:08:12.116
You look like you need one.

712
01:08:12.199 --> 01:08:13.159
Please.

713
01:08:34.430 --> 01:08:35.640
It ain't funny.

714
01:08:35.723 --> 01:08:37.475
I've got loads of cooking to do.

715
01:08:37.558 --> 01:08:38.893
Soldier: You fucking Doris.

716
01:08:38.976 --> 01:08:40.144
Please!

717
01:08:40.227 --> 01:08:41.312
Second Soldier: Run him over!

718
01:08:41.395 --> 01:08:42.730
I want to start cooking.

719
01:08:45.441 --> 01:08:46.359
Jim. Whispering: How's she doing?

720
01:08:48.361 --> 01:08:49.820
Well. she's lost her dad. Jim.

721
01:08:49.904 --> 01:08:51.072
That's how she is.

722
01:08:53.908 --> 01:08:56.577
It's all fucked.

723
01:08:56.661 --> 01:08:57.578
What do you mean?

724
01:09:03.709 --> 01:09:05.127
No. don't do that.
Don't do that. Don't—

725
01:09:05.211 --> 01:09:06.337
Come on. come on. come on. come on.

726
01:09:07.463 --> 01:09:08.422
Hey. don't do that.

727
01:09:11.258 --> 01:09:13.052
Look. Hannah is
what Frank said she is. okay?

728
01:09:13.135 --> 01:09:14.845
She's tough. and she's strong...

729
01:09:14.929 --> 01:09:16.222
and she'll cope
just like I'll cope...

730
01:09:16.305 --> 01:09:17.264
and just like you'll cope.

731
01:09:17.348 --> 01:09:20.142
I don't want her
to have to fucking cope.

732
01:09:21.394 --> 01:09:23.938
I want her to be okay.

733
01:09:25.564 --> 01:09:27.692
When Hannah had her dad.
it was okay.

734
01:09:27.775 --> 01:09:30.528
It was okay for them.
and it was okay for us.

735
01:09:33.948 --> 01:09:35.616
Now it's all just fucked.

736
01:10:07.940 --> 01:10:10.693
So you heard our broadcast?

737
01:10:10.776 --> 01:10:12.069
Yeah. we did.

738
01:10:12.153 --> 01:10:14.155
We must be a disappointment.

739
01:10:14.238 --> 01:10:15.656
You were hoping
for a full brigade...

740
01:10:15.740 --> 01:10:17.616
an army base with helicopters...

741
01:10:17.700 --> 01:10:18.909
and a field hospital.

742
01:10:22.830 --> 01:10:24.498
I was just hoping for—

743
01:10:24.582 --> 01:10:26.584
The answer to infection.

744
01:10:29.170 --> 01:10:30.588
Yeah.

745
01:10:30.671 --> 01:10:33.966
Well. as I said before. it's here...

746
01:10:34.049 --> 01:10:36.051
though it may not be
quite what you imagined.

747
01:10:36.135 --> 01:10:38.012
Just feel very lucky
to have found you.

748
01:10:38.095 --> 01:10:39.096
You were lucky.

749
01:10:39.180 --> 01:10:40.931
The fire drove
hundreds of infected...

750
01:10:41.015 --> 01:10:42.183
out of Manchester.

751
01:10:42.266 --> 01:10:44.351
The surrounding area
is teeming with them.

752
01:10:47.438 --> 01:10:48.397
But don't worry.

753
01:10:50.191 --> 01:10:51.358
You're quite safe here.

754
01:10:55.279 --> 01:10:57.948
West: Flat terrain
all around the house...

755
01:10:58.032 --> 01:10:58.991
floodlights...

756
01:10:59.074 --> 01:11:02.453
which we've rigged up
to a generator...

757
01:11:02.536 --> 01:11:05.122
high perimeter wall. which helps...

758
01:11:05.206 --> 01:11:06.624
and we've been lacing the ground...

759
01:11:06.707 --> 01:11:09.335
with trip wires and land mines.

760
01:11:09.418 --> 01:11:11.128
You wouldn't want to mow the lawn...

761
01:11:11.212 --> 01:11:12.797
but if they get in. we hear them.

762
01:11:17.718 --> 01:11:18.886
Secondary to protection...

763
01:11:18.969 --> 01:11:20.930
our real job is to rebuild...

764
01:11:21.013 --> 01:11:22.473
start again.

765
01:11:22.556 --> 01:11:23.891
The belly of the house...

766
01:11:23.974 --> 01:11:24.934
the heart.

767
01:11:25.017 --> 01:11:25.935
A wood-fired boiler...

768
01:11:26.018 --> 01:11:27.228
providing us with hot water...

769
01:11:27.311 --> 01:11:29.563
the first step towards civilization.

770
01:11:29.647 --> 01:11:30.940
The kitchen.

771
01:11:32.066 --> 01:11:33.275
Soldier: Here. I'll swap you.

772
01:11:33.359 --> 01:11:34.860
A bit of Kendal Mint Cake. right?

773
01:11:34.944 --> 01:11:36.070
Well. wait.
Now. don't be throwing it.

774
01:11:36.153 --> 01:11:37.071
Don't be—

775
01:11:38.322 --> 01:11:39.490
Now. don't be fighting.

776
01:11:39.573 --> 01:11:40.491
Will you put that back?

777
01:11:40.574 --> 01:11:42.159
Put it back.

778
01:11:42.243 --> 01:11:44.662
Jones. our resident tin-opener.

779
01:11:44.745 --> 01:11:46.247
What are you cooking. Jones?

780
01:11:46.330 --> 01:11:47.665
Surprise. sir.

781
01:11:47.748 --> 01:11:49.583
I can't wait.

782
01:11:57.925 --> 01:12:00.177
West: And lastly. meet Mailer.

783
01:12:03.389 --> 01:12:05.975
West: Mailer. Jim.

784
01:12:06.058 --> 01:12:07.810
Jim. Mailer.

785
01:12:09.395 --> 01:12:11.105
Got infected 2 days ago.

786
01:12:12.273 --> 01:12:13.941
Mitchell managed
to knock him out cold...

787
01:12:14.024 --> 01:12:15.317
and we got a chain around his neck.

788
01:12:21.699 --> 01:12:22.700
You're keeping him alive?

789
01:12:24.952 --> 01:12:27.913
The idea was to learn
something about infection...

790
01:12:30.249 --> 01:12:31.292
have him teach me.

791
01:12:39.091 --> 01:12:40.175
And has he?

792
01:12:43.137 --> 01:12:44.096
In a way.

793
01:12:51.812 --> 01:12:54.940
West: He's telling me
he'll never bake bread...

794
01:12:55.024 --> 01:12:57.151
plant crops...

795
01:12:57.234 --> 01:12:58.861
raise livestock.

796
01:12:58.944 --> 01:13:01.822
He's telling me he's futureless...

797
01:13:06.660 --> 01:13:07.578
and eventually...

798
01:13:07.661 --> 01:13:09.413
he'll tell me how long
the infected take...

799
01:13:09.496 --> 01:13:10.414
to starve to death.

800
01:13:42.529 --> 01:13:44.782
Soldier: ♪ Will there be chips
or jacket spuds? ♪

801
01:13:44.865 --> 01:13:47.785
<i>♪ Will there be salad
or frozen peas? ♪</i>

802
01:13:48.869 --> 01:13:50.120
♪ Will there be mushrooms? ♪

803
01:13:50.204 --> 01:13:51.747
♪ Fried onion rings? ♪

804
01:13:51.830 --> 01:13:54.291
Soldiers: ♪ You’ll have
to wait and see ♪

805
01:13:54.375 --> 01:13:56.627
♪ Hope it’s chips.
it’s chips ♪

806
01:13:56.710 --> 01:13:59.505
♪ We hope it’s chips.
it’s chips ♪

807
01:13:59.588 --> 01:14:01.173
♪ We hope it’s chips— ♪

808
01:14:07.846 --> 01:14:09.264
West: Hat.

809
01:14:10.474 --> 01:14:11.600
So...

810
01:14:11.684 --> 01:14:12.726
what have we here?

811
01:14:15.562 --> 01:14:16.981
Tinned ham. tinned peas...

812
01:14:17.064 --> 01:14:18.983
tinned beans. and—

813
01:14:23.737 --> 01:14:24.822
Soldier: Nice one. Doris.

814
01:14:24.905 --> 01:14:26.573
Omelet.

815
01:14:26.657 --> 01:14:27.783
You've prepared a feast. Jones.

816
01:14:27.866 --> 01:14:28.951
Honor of our guests. sir.

817
01:14:29.034 --> 01:14:30.077
Absolutely.

818
01:14:30.160 --> 01:14:32.329
I was going to propose a toast...

819
01:14:32.413 --> 01:14:34.748
but this omelet
will do just as well.

820
01:14:38.210 --> 01:14:39.336
To new friends.

821
01:14:39.420 --> 01:14:40.796
Soldiers: New friends.

822
01:14:51.265 --> 01:14:52.850
Jones. did you notice
while cooking...

823
01:14:52.933 --> 01:14:53.934
that these eggs were off?

824
01:14:55.185 --> 01:14:57.604
I thought the salt
might cover the taste. sir.

825
01:14:58.772 --> 01:15:00.524
Get rid of it.

826
01:15:02.985 --> 01:15:04.028
Soldier: Doris. you twat.

827
01:15:05.362 --> 01:15:07.364
I don't suppose
you can cook. can you?

828
01:15:09.283 --> 01:15:10.868
I can't tell you
how badly we need...

